snippet.textDisplay:
The Coronavirus data in Italy

The Italian Ministry of Health has released new statistics involving COVID 19 in the country.
The data refer to *until March 17*.

The average age of the dead:
- male is 79.5 years.
- for women, 83.7 years, and only 30% of the victims are women.

The victim on average had 2.7 other serious diseases before contracting the virus; 48.5% had three or more diseases. Only three patients (0.8 %) had no other diseases before.

Cancer, heart disease and cerebral haemorrhage were some of the
previous diseases found.
Until March 17, 17 people with
less than 50 years have died:
-5 were under 40 years old;
- all were men
all with severe past diseases,
And
- most common health problems:
pulmonary diseases, cardiovascular diseases,
diabetes, severe obesity and others.
No one under the age of 30
Died.
Of the deceased, 71.1% are from Lombardy,
followed by the Emilia-Romana region
(173%); Veneto (3.9%); Piedmont (1.8%);
and Liguria (1.1%.).

Interestingly, all other regions
have less than 1% of the total dead
